# Playwright (async)

- Use `playwright.async_api` only. Page objects receive `Page` and expose `async` methods.
- Prefer `expect(locator).to_*` assertions with timeouts over raw `wait_for_timeout`.
- Two class-scoped fixtures in `tests/conftest.py` expose a Chromium `BrowserContext` via `self.context`:
  - `browser_context_plain` — vanilla persistent context, no extension loaded.
  - `browser_context_with_extension` — persistent context with the unpacked Prompt Security extension loaded (`--load-extension` / `--disable-extensions-except`) and the popup pre-configured (`#apiDomain`, `#apiKey`, `#saveButton`); resolves the runtime `chrome-extension://<id>` from the MV3 service worker URL and exposes it on `self.chrome_extension_id`.
- Tests open their own tabs via `self.context.new_page()` (one tab per scenario).
- On failure, CI and hooks attach screenshots and page source where possible; traces are under `reports/traces/`.
